answerText: The Great Gatsby[10]  In the novel, Nick Carraway inhabits this region of Long Island, known for its nouveau-riche persona and its high-profile partier, Jay Gatsby. It lies opposite the old-money area where Daisy and Tom Buchanan live.

question: Question:  [10] Name this novel in which Klipspringer phones up Nick Carraway regarding a pair of tennis shoes he left at the protagonist's house prior to his murder. It is by F. Scott Fitzgerald.
